                            <comment id="14708871" author="simonarlott" created="Mon, 24 Aug 2015 06:52:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to return false if any recipient fails attached.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14709016" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Mon, 24 Aug 2015 09:38:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the patch.&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;m not sure it&apos;s safe to change the behaviour like this after so long (it has been like this since before 2.0)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However it obviously makes sense to document the current behaviour.&lt;br/&gt;
And it would perhaps make sense to add a new method to support the new behaviour, though I&apos;m not sure what failures are possible (apart from syntax errors in the email address).&lt;/p&gt;

